text: Not the most amazing coffee nor tea, both felt a bit siap to the taste and I didn’t finish my drink - though it did become better after it was diluted, probably won’t be returning in future.
Best coffee you can find in beauty world area, rich and aromatic. The toasts are equally good and very affordable at $3.90 per set.
Value for money breakfast set. Soft boiled eggs solid york, crispy traditional bread, tea and coffee is a must to have. Many types of sets. Do visit the stall for the full range of food.

ordered set B
- Kaya toast not crispy or properly toasted
- teh siu dai is bland and bitter (tea and milk portion not good)
- egg normal

- ordered additional teh c also bad

The prices are reasonable and fair. The stall owner is incredibly friendly and cheerful. They offer a diverse selection of sets and bread, all of which are enjoyable. However, I deducted one star because the coffee could be improved. Overall, a decent experience
